        • [ - ] Big_Boss - member since 19-Nov-16

          @sailorripley If a shot is goal-bound it will count as a goal for the striker of the ball. For this example, when the ball is directed into the goal while not being goal-bound it will count as an own goal since the keeper directed the ball into the goal after it was not goal-bound anymore. It's a very simple rule.
